parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected deployment of the passenger airbag can cause damage to the vehicle's interior, including the windshield, glove compartment, and rear-view mirror, and can also cause injuries to occupants.
symptoms: damage to the glove compartment door and dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag module can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, may lead to unexpected airbag deployment or failure to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: fragments of black plastic propelled throughout the interior of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system to deploy in the event of an accident can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: airbag sensor light comes on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the ignition switch must be held in the "run" position to keep the engine running
the dash lights may flicker or go out
the vehicle may not restart after stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the navigation system can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The navigation system displays "Downloading" or "Check Disc" messages
the system fails to function properly
the rear camera and other visual displays may be affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the SRS and ABS lights can indicate a problem with the vehicle's safety systems, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The SRS and ABS lights are illuminated on the dashboard
the vehicle's safety systems may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unrelated SRS Electric Control Unit Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS electric control unit can cause the airbag system to malfunction, which can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag system may not function properly
the SRS light may be illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS modulator and accumulator can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, erratic brake performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: erratic brake performance at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Fluid Leakage and Low Brake Fluid Levels
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake fluid leakage and low brake fluid levels can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, erratic brake performance, and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the SRS system can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion and Rust in the Undercarriage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and rust in the undercarriage can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, erratic brake performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rust deposits in the ABS system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, erratic brake performance, and increased risk of accidents.
